      "text": "DarkRaaS is a threat actor specializing in selling unauthorized access to various organizations' systems and networks across multiple countries, with a recent focus on targets in Israel, UAE, Turkey, and South America 4 9 20. The group has been operating for at least six years and typically offers access to sensitive data, internal systems, and infrastructure, with prices ranging up to $25,000 for VPN access 4 9. Their targets span various sectors including government institutions, educational facilities, oil and gas companies, and IT organizations, often claiming to have access to multiple terabytes of sensitive data 7 19."
